class Solution:
    def setZeroes(self, matrix: List[List[int]]) -> None:
        rowset=set()
        colset=set()
        totalrows=len(matrix)
        totalcolumns=len(matrix[0])
        for i in range(totalrows):
            for j in range(totalcolumns):
                if matrix[i][j]==0:
                    rowset.add(i)
                    colset.add(j)
        for i in range(totalrows):
            for j in range(totalcolumns):
                if i in rowset or j in colset:
                    matrix[i][j]=0
            

        
         

    TC -- O(M*N)
     SC -- O(m+n)

When would it be O(m + n)?

If your algorithm only touched each row or each column once, not each cell.
For example:

Scan the first row (O(n))

Scan the first column (O(m))

Do some marking

Update only rows and columns as a block

That’s O(m + n) because you never looked at all m × n cells.
